    <fr:title text="Relative Monad">Relative Monad</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>A monad relative to a profunctor <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathcal  J : \mathcal  D \to  \textrm {Psh} \mathcal  C]]></fr:tex> is a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[T : |\mathcal  C| \to  |\mathcal  D|]]></fr:tex> with operations <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta _X : \mathcal  J(X,TX)]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[-^\dagger  : \mathcal  J(X,TY) \to  \mathcal  D(TX,TY)]]></fr:tex> satisfying three laws <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\eta ^\dagger  = \textrm {id}]]></fr:tex> <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[j^\dagger  \circ  \eta  = j]]></fr:tex> <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(j^\dagger  \circ  k)^\dagger  = j^\dagger  \circ  k^\dagger ]]></fr:tex></html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
